The paper presents a method for identifying genetic patterns from multiple large-scale genomic datasets, which involves matrix recovery and optimization algorithms. This work is related to machine learning and data mining, particularly in the areas of matrix factorization and low-rank matrix recovery, which are covered by the arXiv categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases). The paper also deals with the analysis of complex diseases and genetic correlations, which are relevant to the arXiv categories of cs.CE (Computational Biology and Bioinformatics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
